#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_enchanting/init.lua:234
msgid ""
"Enchanting Tables will let you enchant armors, tools, weapons, and books "
"with various abilities. But, at the cost of some experience, and lapis "
"lazuli."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_enchanting/init.lua:236
msgid "Rightclick the Enchanting Table to open the enchanting menu."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_enchanting/init.lua:237
msgid ""
"Place a tool, armor, weapon or book into the top left slot, and then place "
"1-3 Lapis Lazuli in the slot to the right."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_enchanting/init.lua:238
msgid ""
"After placing your items in the slots, the enchanting options will be shown. "
"Hover over the options to read what is available to you."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_enchanting/init.lua:239
msgid ""
"These options are randomized, and dependent on experience level; but the "
"enchantment strength can be increased."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_enchanting/init.lua:240
msgid ""
"To increase the enchantment strength, place bookshelves around the "
"enchanting table. However, you will need to keep 1 air node between the "
"table, & the bookshelves to empower the enchanting table."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_enchanting/init.lua:241
msgid ""
"After finally selecting your enchantment; left-click on the selection, and "
"you will see both the lapis lazuli and your experience levels consumed. And, "
"an enchanted item left in its place."
msgstr ""

